---
source: crates/normalize/tests/cli_snapshots.rs
expression: "snapshot_help(&[\"sessions\"])"
---
Review AI agent session logs. Use to check cost, duration, and tool usage across coding sessions.

Usage: normalize sessions [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  list       List available sessions
  show       Show a specific session (summary or full conversation)
  analyze    Run deep behavioral analysis on a session (tool stats, errors, token costs, corrections)
  stats      Show aggregate statistics across sessions
  messages   Extract all messages across sessions into a flat, queryable form
  subagents  List subagents for a given parent session
  patterns   Analyze tool call sequence patterns across sessions using Markov chain transition matrices
  plans      List and view agent plans
  help       Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --pretty                     Human-friendly output with colors and formatting
      --compact                    Compact output without colors (overrides TTY detection)
      --jsonl                      Output one JSON object per line (for arrays)
      --json                       Output machine-readable JSON
      --jq <jq>                    Filter output through jq expression
      --input-schema               Print JSON Schema of the subcommand's input parameters and exit
      --output-schema              Print JSON Schema of the subcommand's return type and exit
      --params-json <params-json>  Provide all parameters as a JSON object instead of individual flags
  -h, --help                       Print help
  -V, --version                    Print version
